<DocsLayout
  title="CVE Command — vulnex docs"
  description="Search, list, fetch, and track CVEs from the National Vulnerability Database using the vulnex CLI."
>
  <Fragment slot="sidebar">
    <span class="sidebar-heading">CVE Command</span>
    <a href="#overview">Overview</a>
    <a href="#cve-get">cve get</a>
    <a href="#cve-search">cve search</a>
    <a href="#cve-list">cve list</a>
    <a href="#cve-history">cve history</a>
    <a href="#cve-watch">cve watch</a>
    <span class="sidebar-heading">Reference</span>
    <a href="#global-flags">Global flags</a>
    <a href="#output-formats">Output formats</a>
    <a href="#scoring">Scoring profiles</a>
    <a href="#tips">Tips &amp; recipes</a>
  </Fragment>

  <!-- ── Overview ─────────────────────────── -->
  <section id="overview">
    <span class="doc-badge">Command Reference</span>
    <h1>vulnex cve</h1>
    <p class="doc-lead">
      Search, list, and fetch detailed CVE information from the
      <a href="https://nvd.nist.gov/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">National Vulnerability Database</a>.
      Five subcommands cover every CVE workflow — from one-off lookups to bulk triage and persistent watch lists.
    </p>

    <div class="subcommand-grid">
      <a href="#cve-get" class="subcommand-card">
        <h3>cve get</h3>
        <p>Fetch one or more CVEs by ID</p>
      </a>
      <a href="#cve-search" class="subcommand-card">
        <h3>cve search</h3>
        <p>Keyword search with filters</p>
      </a>
      <a href="#cve-list" class="subcommand-card">
        <h3>cve list</h3>
        <p>Browse CVEs with pagination</p>
      </a>
      <a href="#cve-history" class="subcommand-card">
        <h3>cve history</h3>
        <p>Modification timeline for a CVE</p>
      </a>
      <a href="#cve-watch" class="subcommand-card">
        <h3>cve watch</h3>
        <p>Persistent local watch list</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="doc-divider" />

  <!-- ── cve get ──────────────────────────── -->
  <section id="cve-get">
    <h2>cve get</h2>
    <p>Fetch one or more CVEs from NVD by their ID. Returns CVSS scores, descriptions, CWEs, references, and affected products. For multi-source enrichment (EPSS, KEV, GHSA, OSV), use <code>vulnex enrich</code> instead.</p>

    <h3>Usage</h3>
    <div class="code-inline"><code>vulnex cve get &lt;CVE-ID...&gt; [flags]</code></div>

    <h3>Examples</h3>
    <TerminalWindow title="cve get — single CVE">
      <pre><span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">vulnex cve get</span> <span class="t-cve">CVE-2021-44228</span>

 <span class="t-cve"><strong>CVE-2021-44228</strong></span> — Apache Log4j2 JNDI features do not protect
 against attacker controlled LDAP and other JNDI related endpoints

 <span class="t-label">Severity</span>       <span class="t-critical">CRITICAL (10.0)</span>
 <span class="t-label">Vector</span>         NETWORK / LOW / NONE / CHANGED
 <span class="t-label">Published</span>      2021-12-10
 <span class="t-label">Modified</span>       2023-11-06
 <span class="t-label">Source</span>         NVD

 <span class="t-dim">Affected Versions</span>
   <span class="t-value">apache:log4j</span>   &gt;= 2.0, &lt; 2.15.0

 <span class="t-dim">References</span>
   https://logging.apache.org/log4j/2.x/security.html <span class="t-label">[Vendor Advisory]</span>
   https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-jfh8-c2jp-5v3q <span class="t-label">[Patch]</span>
   <span class="t-dim">(3 more...)</span></pre>
    </TerminalWindow>

    <TerminalWindow title="cve get — multiple CVEs as JSON">
      <pre><span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">vulnex cve get</span> <span class="t-cve">CVE-2024-3094 CVE-2023-44228</span> <span class="t-flag">--output json</span></pre>
    </TerminalWindow>

    <TerminalWindow title="cve get — from stdin">
      <pre><span class="t-prompt">$</span> echo <span class="t-cve">"CVE-2024-3094"</span> | <span class="t-cmd">vulnex cve get</span> <span class="t-flag">--stdin</span></pre>
    </TerminalWindow>

    <TerminalWindow title="cve get — with scoring profile">
      <pre><span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">vulnex cve get</span> <span class="t-cve">CVE-2024-24790</span> <span class="t-flag">--scoring-profile exploit-focused</span>

 <span class="t-label">Weighted Score:</span> <span class="t-value">11.0/100</span> <span class="t-dim">(profile: exploit-focused, weights: CVSS=0.10 EPSS=0.60 KEV=0.30)</span></pre>
    </TerminalWindow>

    <h3>Flags</h3>
    <div class="flags-table">
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Flag</th><th>Type</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>--stdin</code></td><td>bool</td><td>false</td><td>Read CVE IDs from stdin (one per line)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--scoring-profile</code></td><td>string</td><td>—</td><td>Preset weight balance for scoring: <code>default</code> (balanced), <code>exploit-focused</code>, or <code>severity-focused</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--cvss-weight</code></td><td>float</td><td>—</td><td>How much severity (CVSS) influences the final score, from 0.0 (ignore) to 1.0 (full weight)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--epss-weight</code></td><td>float</td><td>—</td><td>How much exploit probability (EPSS) influences the final score, from 0.0 (ignore) to 1.0 (full weight)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--kev-weight</code></td><td>float</td><td>—</td><td>How much known-exploited status (KEV) influences the final score, from 0.0 (ignore) to 1.0 (full weight)</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="doc-divider" />

  <!-- ── cve search ───────────────────────── -->
  <section id="cve-search">
    <h2>cve search</h2>
    <p>Search the National Vulnerability Database by keyword. Results are sorted newest-first and can be filtered by severity, year, CWE, and KEV membership.</p>

    <h3>Usage</h3>
    <div class="code-inline"><code>vulnex cve search &lt;query&gt; [flags]</code></div>

    <h3>Examples</h3>
    <TerminalWindow title="cve search — keyword">
      <pre><span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">vulnex cve search</span> <span class="t-value">"apache log4j"</span></pre>
    </TerminalWindow>

    <TerminalWindow title="cve search — with filters">
      <pre><span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">vulnex cve search</span> <span class="t-value">"remote code execution"</span> <span class="t-flag">--severity critical --has-kev</span>

 <span class="t-dim">Found 42 results (showing 20)</span>

 <span class="t-cve">CVE-2021-44228</span>  <span class="t-critical">CRITICAL</span>  Apache Log4j2 JNDI features do not protect...
 <span class="t-cve">CVE-2024-3094</span>   <span class="t-critical">CRITICAL</span>  Malicious code in xz/liblzma leading to...
 <span class="t-cve">CVE-2023-46604</span>  <span class="t-critical">CRITICAL</span>  Apache ActiveMQ is vulnerable to Remote...
 <span class="t-dim">...</span></pre>
    </TerminalWindow>

    <TerminalWindow title="cve search — filter by year and CWE">
      <pre><span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">vulnex cve search</span> <span class="t-value">"xss"</span> <span class="t-flag">--cwe CWE-79 --year 2024 --limit 50</span></pre>
    </TerminalWindow>

    <TerminalWindow title="cve search — export to JSON">
      <pre><span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">vulnex cve search</span> <span class="t-value">"fortinet"</span> <span class="t-flag">--year 2024 --output json</span> > fortinet-cves.json</pre>
    </TerminalWindow>

    <h3>Flags</h3>
    <div class="flags-table">
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Flag</th><th>Type</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>--severity</code></td><td>string</td><td>—</td><td>Filter by severity: <code>LOW</code>, <code>MEDIUM</code>, <code>HIGH</code>, <code>CRITICAL</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--has-kev</code></td><td>bool</td><td>false</td><td>Only show CVEs in CISA KEV catalog</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--year</code></td><td>string</td><td>—</td><td>Filter by publication year (e.g., <code>2024</code>)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--cwe</code></td><td>string</td><td>—</td><td>Filter by CWE ID (e.g., <code>CWE-79</code>)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--no-rejected</code></td><td>bool</td><td>true</td><td>Exclude rejected CVEs</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--limit</code></td><td>int</td><td>20</td><td>Maximum results to return</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="doc-divider" />

  <!-- ── cve list ─────────────────────────── -->
  <section id="cve-list">
    <h2>cve list</h2>
    <p>Browse CVEs from NVD with pagination and optional date/severity filters. Use <code>--offset</code> to paginate through large result sets.</p>

    <h3>Usage</h3>
    <div class="code-inline"><code>vulnex cve list [flags]</code></div>

    <h3>Examples</h3>
    <TerminalWindow title="cve list — critical CVEs">
      <pre><span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">vulnex cve list</span> <span class="t-flag">--severity critical --limit 50</span></pre>
    </TerminalWindow>

    <TerminalWindow title="cve list — date range">
      <pre><span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">vulnex cve list</span> <span class="t-flag">--start-date 2024-01-01 --end-date 2024-12-31</span></pre>
    </TerminalWindow>

    <TerminalWindow title="cve list — pagination">
      <pre><span class="t-dim"># Page 1</span>
<span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">vulnex cve list</span> <span class="t-flag">--limit 20</span>

<span class="t-dim"># Page 2</span>
<span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">vulnex cve list</span> <span class="t-flag">--offset 20 --limit 20</span>

<span class="t-dim"># Page 3</span>
<span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">vulnex cve list</span> <span class="t-flag">--offset 40 --limit 20</span></pre>
    </TerminalWindow>

    <h3>Flags</h3>
    <div class="flags-table">
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Flag</th><th>Type</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>--severity</code></td><td>string</td><td>—</td><td>Filter by severity: <code>LOW</code>, <code>MEDIUM</code>, <code>HIGH</code>, <code>CRITICAL</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--start-date</code></td><td>string</td><td>—</td><td>Publication start date (<code>YYYY-MM-DD</code>)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--end-date</code></td><td>string</td><td>—</td><td>Publication end date (<code>YYYY-MM-DD</code>)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--no-rejected</code></td><td>bool</td><td>true</td><td>Exclude rejected CVEs</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--limit</code></td><td>int</td><td>20</td><td>Results per page</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--offset</code></td><td>int</td><td>0</td><td>Starting offset for pagination</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="doc-divider" />

  <!-- ── cve history ──────────────────────── -->
  <section id="cve-history">
    <h2>cve history</h2>
    <p>Show the modification history of a CVE from NVD, including status changes and CVSS score revisions over time.</p>

    <h3>Usage</h3>
    <div class="code-inline"><code>vulnex cve history &lt;CVE-ID&gt;</code></div>

    <h3>Examples</h3>
    <TerminalWindow title="cve history">
      <pre><span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">vulnex cve history</span> <span class="t-cve">CVE-2021-44228</span>

 <span class="t-label">CVE ID</span>        <span class="t-cve">CVE-2021-44228</span>
 <span class="t-label">Status</span>        Modified
 <span class="t-label">Published</span>     2021-12-10
 <span class="t-label">Last Modified</span> 2023-11-06

 <span class="t-dim">Change History:</span>
 <span class="t-label">Source</span>        nvd@nist.gov
 <span class="t-label">Tags</span>          Vendor Advisory, Third Party Advisory

 <span class="t-dim">CVSS Score History:</span>
 <span class="t-label">Version</span>  <span class="t-label">Severity</span>    <span class="t-label">Score</span>  <span class="t-label">Source</span>
 v3.1     <span class="t-critical">CRITICAL</span>    10.0   nvd@nist.gov
 v2.0     HIGH        9.3    nvd@nist.gov</pre>
    </TerminalWindow>

    <TerminalWindow title="cve history — JSON output">
      <pre><span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">vulnex cve history</span> <span class="t-cve">CVE-2024-3094</span> <span class="t-flag">--output json</span></pre>
    </TerminalWindow>

    <p class="doc-note">This command accepts exactly one CVE ID. No subcommand-specific flags beyond global flags.</p>
  </section>

  <hr class="doc-divider" />

  <!-- ── cve watch ────────────────────────── -->
  <section id="cve-watch">
    <h2>cve watch</h2>
    <p>Manage a persistent local watch list of CVEs. Watched CVEs are stored in the local SQLite cache and can be refreshed on demand to pull the latest data.</p>

    <h3>Usage</h3>
    <div class="code-inline"><code>vulnex cve watch &lt;CVE-ID...&gt; [flags]</code></div>

    <h3>Examples</h3>
    <TerminalWindow title="cve watch — add CVEs">
      <pre><span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">vulnex cve watch</span> <span class="t-cve">CVE-2024-3094 CVE-2021-44228</span>

 <span class="t-value">Added 2 CVEs to watch list (4 total)</span></pre>
    </TerminalWindow>

    <TerminalWindow title="cve watch — list watched CVEs">
      <pre><span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">vulnex cve watch</span> <span class="t-flag">--list</span>

 <span class="t-dim">4 CVEs in watch list:</span>
 <span class="t-cve">CVE-2021-44228</span>
 <span class="t-cve">CVE-2024-3094</span>
 <span class="t-cve">CVE-2023-46604</span>
 <span class="t-cve">CVE-2024-24790</span></pre>
    </TerminalWindow>

    <TerminalWindow title="cve watch — refresh all">
      <pre><span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">vulnex cve watch</span> <span class="t-flag">--refresh</span>

 <span class="t-dim">Refreshing 4 watched CVEs...</span>
 <span class="t-cve">CVE-2021-44228</span>  <span class="t-critical">CRITICAL (10.0)</span>  Apache Log4j2 JNDI features...
 <span class="t-cve">CVE-2024-3094</span>   <span class="t-critical">CRITICAL (10.0)</span>  Malicious code in xz/liblzma...
 <span class="t-cve">CVE-2023-46604</span>  <span class="t-critical">CRITICAL (10.0)</span>  Apache ActiveMQ RCE...
 <span class="t-cve">CVE-2024-24790</span>  <span class="t-critical">CRITICAL (9.8)</span>   net/netip: unexpected behavior...</pre>
    </TerminalWindow>

    <TerminalWindow title="cve watch — remove + stdin">
      <pre><span class="t-dim"># Remove a CVE</span>
<span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">vulnex cve watch</span> <span class="t-flag">--remove</span> <span class="t-cve">CVE-2024-3094</span>
 <span class="t-value">Removed 1, 3 remaining</span>

<span class="t-dim"># Add from file</span>
<span class="t-prompt">$</span> cat critical-cves.txt | <span class="t-cmd">vulnex cve watch</span> <span class="t-flag">--stdin</span></pre>
    </TerminalWindow>

    <h3>Flags</h3>
    <div class="flags-table">
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Flag</th><th>Type</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>--list</code></td><td>bool</td><td>false</td><td>List all watched CVEs</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--refresh</code></td><td>bool</td><td>false</td><td>Re-fetch data for all watched CVEs</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--remove</code></td><td>bool</td><td>false</td><td>Remove CVEs from the watch list</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--stdin</code></td><td>bool</td><td>false</td><td>Read CVE IDs from stdin</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <p class="doc-note">The watch list requires the local cache to be enabled (it is by default). Use <code>--cache-dir</code> to customize the storage location.</p>
  </section>

  <hr class="doc-divider" />

  <!-- ── Global Flags ─────────────────────── -->
  <section id="global-flags">
    <h2>Global flags</h2>
    <p>These flags apply to all <code>vulnex</code> commands, including every <code>cve</code> subcommand.</p>

    <div class="flags-table">
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Flag</th><th>Type</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>-o, --output</code></td><td>string</td><td>table</td><td>Output format: <code>table</code>, <code>json</code>, <code>csv</code>, <code>markdown</code>, <code>yaml</code>, <code>sarif</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>-l, --long</code></td><td>bool</td><td>false</td><td>Show full descriptions instead of truncated</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--no-color</code></td><td>bool</td><td>false</td><td>Disable colored output</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--api-key</code></td><td>string</td><td>—</td><td>NVD API key (overrides config/env)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--config</code></td><td>string</td><td>—</td><td>Path to config file</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--cache-dir</code></td><td>string</td><td>—</td><td>Custom cache directory</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--no-cache</code></td><td>bool</td><td>false</td><td>Bypass cache for this request</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--offline</code></td><td>bool</td><td>false</td><td>Only use locally cached data</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--timeout</code></td><td>duration</td><td>—</td><td>HTTP timeout (e.g., <code>30s</code>, <code>1m</code>)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>-v, --verbose</code></td><td>bool</td><td>false</td><td>Verbose debug output</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>-q, --quiet</code></td><td>bool</td><td>false</td><td>Suppress non-essential output</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="doc-divider" />

  <!-- ── Output Formats ───────────────────── -->
  <section id="output-formats">
    <h2>Output formats</h2>
    <p>Use the <code>-o</code> / <code>--output</code> flag to switch between formats. All CVE subcommands support every format.</p>

    <div class="format-grid">
      <div class="format-card">
        <h4>table</h4>
        <p>Color-coded terminal table. Default output for interactive use.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="format-card">
        <h4>json</h4>
        <p>Pretty-printed JSON. Ideal for scripting and jq pipelines.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="format-card">
        <h4>csv</h4>
        <p>Comma-separated values. Import into spreadsheets or pipe to <code>cut</code>.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="format-card">
        <h4>markdown</h4>
        <p>Markdown tables. Paste directly into GitHub issues or reports.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="format-card">
        <h4>yaml</h4>
        <p>YAML output. Good for config files and readable structured data.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="format-card">
        <h4>sarif</h4>
        <p>SARIF v2.1.0. Upload to GitHub Code Scanning or Azure DevOps.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <TerminalWindow title="Output format examples">
      <pre><span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">vulnex cve get</span> <span class="t-cve">CVE-2021-44228</span> <span class="t-flag">-o json</span> | jq '.severity'
<span class="t-value">"CRITICAL"</span>

<span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">vulnex cve search</span> <span class="t-value">"log4j"</span> <span class="t-flag">-o csv</span> > results.csv

<span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">vulnex cve list</span> <span class="t-flag">--severity critical -o markdown</span> >> report.md</pre>
    </TerminalWindow>
  </section>

  <hr class="doc-divider" />

  <!-- ── Scoring ──────────────────────────── -->
  <section id="scoring">
    <h2>Scoring profiles</h2>
    <p>When using <code>cve get</code> with <code>--scoring-profile</code>, vulnex computes a weighted risk score blending CVSS, EPSS, and KEV signals.</p>

    <div class="scoring-table">
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Profile</th><th>CVSS</th><th>EPSS</th><th>KEV</th><th>Use case</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>default</code></td><td>0.30</td><td>0.50</td><td>0.20</td><td>Balanced — exploitation probability is the strongest signal</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>exploit-focused</code></td><td>0.10</td><td>0.60</td><td>0.30</td><td>Prioritize active exploitation signals</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>severity-focused</code></td><td>0.60</td><td>0.30</td><td>0.10</td><td>Weight CVSS severity highest</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <p>You can also set custom weights that override the profile:</p>

    <TerminalWindow title="Custom scoring weights">
      <pre><span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">vulnex cve get</span> <span class="t-cve">CVE-2024-24790</span> \
    <span class="t-flag">--cvss-weight 0.5 --epss-weight 0.3 --kev-weight 0.2</span></pre>
    </TerminalWindow>

    <h3>Formula</h3>
    <div class="formula-block">
      <code>score = (cvss/10 × cvssWeight + epss × epssWeight + kev × kevWeight) × 100</code>
    </div>
    <p class="doc-note">Where <code>kev</code> is 1 if the CVE is in CISA's Known Exploited Vulnerabilities catalog, 0 otherwise. The result is clamped to [0, 100].</p>
  </section>

  <hr class="doc-divider" />

  <!-- ── Tips ─────────────────────────────── -->
  <section id="tips">
    <h2>Tips &amp; recipes</h2>

    <h3>Pipe CVE IDs between commands</h3>
    <TerminalWindow title="Piping workflow">
      <pre><span class="t-dim"># Search → get full details</span>
<span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">vulnex cve search</span> <span class="t-value">"log4j"</span> <span class="t-flag">-o csv</span> \
    | cut -d, -f1 \
    | <span class="t-cmd">vulnex cve get</span> <span class="t-flag">--stdin -o json</span>

<span class="t-dim"># Watch all critical CVEs from a search</span>
<span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">vulnex cve search</span> <span class="t-value">"apache"</span> <span class="t-flag">--severity critical -o csv</span> \
    | cut -d, -f1 \
    | <span class="t-cmd">vulnex cve watch</span> <span class="t-flag">--stdin</span></pre>
    </TerminalWindow>

    <h3>Offline mode</h3>
    <TerminalWindow title="Cache then go offline">
      <pre><span class="t-dim"># Warm the cache while online</span>
<span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">vulnex cve get</span> <span class="t-cve">CVE-2021-44228</span>

<span class="t-dim"># Later, query without network</span>
<span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">vulnex</span> <span class="t-flag">--offline</span> <span class="t-cmd">cve get</span> <span class="t-cve">CVE-2021-44228</span></pre>
    </TerminalWindow>

    <h3>NVD API key</h3>
    <p>Without an API key, NVD rate-limits you to ~5 requests per 30 seconds. With a key, that jumps to ~50. Set it once:</p>
    <TerminalWindow title="Set NVD API key">
      <pre><span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">vulnex config set</span> api_keys.nvd <span class="t-value">"your-key-here"</span>

<span class="t-dim"># Or use env var / flag</span>
<span class="t-prompt">$</span> export VULNEX_API_KEY=<span class="t-value">"your-key-here"</span>
<span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">vulnex</span> <span class="t-flag">--api-key "your-key-here"</span> <span class="t-cmd">cve search</span> <span class="t-value">"log4j"</span></pre>
    </TerminalWindow>

    <h3>Export for reporting</h3>
    <TerminalWindow title="Export recipes">
      <pre><span class="t-dim"># Markdown table for a report</span>
<span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">vulnex cve search</span> <span class="t-value">"fortinet"</span> <span class="t-flag">--year 2024 -o markdown</span> >> report.md

<span class="t-dim"># CSV for spreadsheet import</span>
<span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">vulnex cve list</span> <span class="t-flag">--severity critical -o csv</span> > critical.csv

<span class="t-dim"># SARIF for GitHub Code Scanning</span>
<span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">vulnex cve get</span> <span class="t-cve">CVE-2021-44228</span> <span class="t-flag">-o sarif</span> > results.sarif</pre>
    </TerminalWindow>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>

